  "prompt": "What is the best mobile ad networks in japan?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, several mobile ad networks are prominent and effective in Japan. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **AdMob (Google)**: As one of the largest mobile ad networks, AdMob offers a wide reach and various ad formats suitable for app monetization.\n\n2. **Facebook Audience Network**: Leveraging Facebook's vast user data, this network allows app developers to monetize their apps with targeted ads.\n\n3. **Millennial Media**: Known for its strong presence in the mobile advertising space, it offers a variety of advertising solutions and analytics tools.\n\n4. **Criteo**: Though it focuses on performance-based advertising, Criteo can help drive user engagement and conversion with its personalized ad solutions.\n\n5. **Tapjoy**: This network specializes in incentivized advertising, often used in mobile games, offering rewards for user engagement.\n\n6. **Adjust**: While primarily an analytics and attribution platform, Adjust also allows for ad monetization through its partnerships with various networks.\n\n7. **InMobi**: This network provides a wide range of ad formats and has a strong presence in Asia, including Japan.\n\n8. **Vungle**: Specializing in in-app video ads, Vungle is widely used in gaming apps to drive user retention and monetization.\n\n9. **AdColony**: Focused on mobile video advertising, AdColony offers high-quality video ads that are particularly effective for engaging users.\n\n10. **Dentsu**: As a major advertising agency in Japan, Dentsu provides various digital advertising solutions, including mobile ads tailored for the Japanese market.\n\nThese networks each have their strengths and may be suitable depending on your specific objectives, target audience, and types of apps. Always consider testing multiple ad networks to determine which one provides the best performance for your particular needs.",
